text: Micaela Bouter (born 27 October 1995) is a South African diver. She competed in the women's 3 metre springboard event at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. She finished in 35th place in the preliminary round. She attended and competed in diving at the University of Houston. ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:South African female divers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
